The "Swallowing the exception" is a bit alarming at first. It's true that if this method returns false then `TestUtils.waitForCondition` (which is using this method as the test condition) will fail at line 137.

Pretty minor, but how about the following?
```
            // Log the exception and return that the partitions were not assigned
            log.error("Could not check connector state info.", e);
            return false;
```

